arts.ttl: Indian Wells: Jack Draper stuns Carlos Alcaraz to reach first Masters 1000 final and move into world's top 10
arts.sum: Draper will pay 12th-seeded Dane Holger Rune in Sunday's final - live on Sky Sports Tennis from 9pm - after earning his second career win over four-time Grand Slam champion Alcaraz, who has also emerged triumphant at Indian Wells in each of the last two years. Jack Draper booked a first ever Masters 1000 final and a place in the world's top 10 as he beat Carlos Alcaraz 6-1 0-6 6-4 in a thrilling semi final at Indian Wells.

arts.ttl: O'Brien rescues a point for Everton against West Ham
arts.sum: Jake O’Brien’s late header saw Everton salvage a 1-1 draw against West Ham United and stretch their Premier League unbeaten run to nine matches. The draw moves Everton above Manchester United – who play on Sunday – into 14th, two places above West Ham courtesy of a better goal difference.
